def single_distr(column,df,title):
    sns.set()
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,18))
    sns.distplot(df[column],bins=20)
    plt.title(title)

#deciding the number of clusters

wcss = []

for i in range(1, 11):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters = i, 
                    max_iter = 400)
    kmeans.fit(x)
    wcss.append(kmeans.inertia_)
    

plt.plot(range(1, 11), wcss)
plt.title('Elbow Method')
plt.xlabel('Association')
plt.ylabel('WCSS') 
plt.show()

Based off the above, I am going to use 4 clusters for this segmentation

Initial Thoughts:

Segment 0: Early adopters, greatest number of purhcases & money spent (Target Customers)

Segment 1: Newer customers (New Customers)

Segment 2: Second greatest volume of books purchased & spend, have been customers for a substantial amount of time (Old Reliable Customers)

Segment 3: Have been customers for a long time, but haven't made purchases in awhile (Reluctant Customers)
